Three people were injured one seriously so, after the vehicle they were in left the roadway colliding into a light pole on Saturday evening. Rescue Care&#8217;s Garrith Jamieson said paramedics responded to the scene around 11:30 pm on Saturday night on Crompton road.Paramedics rashed to the scene to find a single vehicle that had crashed. Three passengers had been injured with one sustaining serious injuries.Advanced Life Support Paramedics worked to stabilise the injured on the scene before transporting them through to a nearby hospital for the further care that they required.At this stage the exact cause of the collision is unknown however SAPS were on the scene and will be investigating further.